❄️Who loves cold baths? Or at least, who has the classic love-hate relationship with ‘em?

I personally integrate cold therapy into my daily routine for several reasons (and have for nearly 20 years, since my days as a chilly open water swimmer and triathlete), including: 
👉🏼 Boosted metabolism
👉🏼 Enhanced immune function
👉🏼 Better vagal nerve tone
👉🏼 Creation of metabolically active brown fat
👉🏼 Improved cardiovascular fitness
👉🏼 Elevated mood & focus (like a full body cup o’ coffee!)

Anyways, I have a @morozkoforge set up at my house that I keep at around 32 degrees (this bad boy is self cleaning and maintains super cold temps even in high heat summer conditions).👉🏼In this video, I share some tips and tricks for plunging without over-activating your nervous system or turning yourself into a hyperventilating freak-out fest.

😆If you're not sure where to start when it comes to integrating cold therapy into your routine, then I've ALSO got a cool (hehe) opportunity for you to learn everything you need to know about cold thermogenesis👇🏼. 

My company @kion has officially kicked off their Cold Thermo Challenge! By signing up for the challenge, you’ll learn everything you need to know from experts in cold therapy so you can practice it safely and effectively.👏🏼You'll also automatically enter for a chance to win a bundle of prizes which includes a signed copy of my book, Boundless. 

💥Click the link in my bio to take the plunge, and join thousands of others. How about you? Do you even cold plunge, bro? 😉

😁I’m going to tell you a few things you might not know about my new Boundless Cookbook (Including the thousands and thousands of dollars spent in a test kitchen to make sure all the recipes are just perfect).

👉🏼Enjoy this quick video, and if you didn’t get the book yet, it’s now available on Amazon, and also on BoundlessCookbook.com (click the link in my bio).

If you already got yourself a copy and you’re enjoying the mouthwatering goodness within, please be so kind as to leave the book a review on Amazon🙏🏼. That is so, so helpful for getting the word out and helping thousands of people around the world and their families to eat healthy and enjoy doing it!

By the way, I’m curious to hear from you… What is your all-time favorite meal to prepare, or what would you eat, for example, if you had to take one thing to a desert island for the rest of your life👇🏼?

This recipe is a “biohacked”, simplified way to amplify the flavor of any stew meat or roast meat😋. It’s a fast and easy way to feed yourself or the whole family for days, since the stew tastes even better in the days after it cooks!
 
👉🏼Braising the meat with maple syrup and vinegar gives the roast plenty of time to get fall-apart tender while all that flavor sinks deep into the meat!

💥As a bonus, the braising liquid reduces to a thick, concentrated sauce to pour over the meat on your plate and add extra flavor to the caramelized vegetables as well.
 
The “secret sauces” are a few I use in other recipes within the brand new Boundless Cookbook👉🏼: namely grass-fed, grass-finished beef and bacon from @belcampomeatco meats, @kettleandfire organic bone broth, the antioxidant rich @Organifi red juice powder, a touch of organic @joeyshotsauce Sauce, the incredible, antioxidant rich Himalayan Tartary Buckwheat flour and equally anti-oxidant rich @FourSigmatic Chaga mushroom extract, Fresh Pressed Olive Oil club extra virgin olive oil, and a bit of the incredibly flavorful @avajaneskitchen salt from the Mexican coast.
 
😁Finally, as an optional add-on, for an incredibly even cook with no “hotspots”, I like to cook with my dutch pot and vegetables on the @traegergrills , although an oven will also do!
 
Click the link in my bio for this full recipe💥!

Biohacking testosterone has been a hot topic for the past few years👀....Er, decades. Er, centuries. Perhaps technology and social media have just made what men and women have possibly pursued since the dawn of time just a bit more in our faces.

You can find plenty of research articles on optimizing testosterone and even a bunch of books and e-books boasting the latest and greatest ways to boost your testosterone📖. 

Don't even get me started on supplement companies, who mostly source cheap herbs from Asia, shove them into a bottle, and produce a very, very sexy website designed to get you to empty your wallet to pop some magical boosting pill😬.

You would be shocked at the amount of blood work I see that shows me men and women who are doing everything they read on the internet to boost testosterone with barely a bump in total or free levels of this hormone👈🏼.

💥However, I commonly see a very basic problem in many of the labs I review....and that is nutrient deficiency— specifically, the nutrients listed above: magnesium, creatine, DHEA, boron, Vitamin D and Zinc. Most folks oughta prioritize these before even thinking about some kind of hormone replacement therapy.. 

👉🏼Click the link in my bio to learn more about optimal nutrient levels for healthy testosterone production and much more! Have you struggled with optimizing testosterone in the past? What has helped you?

Plants are so smart🌱. Plants, herbs, flowers, roots, leaves and other elements of green nature are communicating with us and each other in remarkable ways.

In fact, I recently learned from a podcast guest that every plant has an electromagnetic dimension to it and does a lot of communicating within itself and between other plants too⚡️. 

A pretty fascinating example of this is how plants communicate when it comes to pests. Suppose a pest starts eating one of the plants in a natural environment. That plant can then send an electromagnetic pulse that triggers aromatic compounds to communicate to other neighboring plants, warning them of the pest.

Plants can communicate via organic compounds like volatile oils. Interestingly, your heart can detect the electromagnetic field emanated by plants, which says a lot for listening to your gut and heart and tuning into the sacred intelligence of plants around you👈🏼.

This same intelligence may have even been what helped our ancestors tap into using certain plants for different ailments.

Sounds pretty 'woo woo' right? I thought so at first, until I got my hands on this eye-opening book called Evolutionary Herbalism📖.

I recently sat down with the author of Evolutionary Herbalism and expert herbalist Sajah Popham to discuss the whole concept of sacred intelligence of plants, how a disconnection between the human and plant kingdom has helped to create some of the chaos we see today, and much more.

💥Click the link in my bio to dive into this conversation!

node.text:
I have identified that I have a problem👇🏼.

See, I'm a loner. Always have been. I'm just one of those guys who doesn't need to be with people or be around people to be happy.

A social butterfly I am not. At least, that's the story I've been telling myself for a long, long time👀.

However, I've been thinking quite a bit lately about the power of shared experiences.

⚡️Shared experiences allow us to savor God’s creation in a far more amplified way than we’re able to do if we are simply wandering this planet by ourselves, dependent upon nobody, but also connected to nobody.

💥In today's Sabbath Ramblings, you'll discover what constitutes shared experiences, why I have resisted them in the past, and my current thoughts on cooking, eating, learning, competing, and more with others.

👉🏼Click the link in my bio to dive into the full article. And what about you? Are you introverted and do you identify with my own realization that I’ve been living much of my life scared of shared experiences?
